<xref keyref="03adju001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-5C85D6FC-5E14-4490-AB29-1EEC54BC3FB5.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 03 How to adjust the print height (calibration)?>03 How to adjust the print height (calibration)</xref> 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">With this test the offsets for the Z motion system height can be set. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The object is to measure two offsets manually and enter the values in this test. This test will then compute and apply the offsets necessary to get the distance between the nozzle plates and the print surface within specification. You may open the top cover when the test asks for the measurements. If the test ended successfully the new offsets are applied, and you can measure again to check the result. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Press Continue when you are done verifying. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-CF054B8F-4DEF-450F-B061-20C1798FD6DE.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SDS</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
